amily Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Mello","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Manuel, Jose, Carlos, Adelino, Ana, Joaquin, Acacio, Claudio, Cristina, Fernando, Americo, Enrique.  Portuguese Duarte, Joaquim, Armanda, Joao, Paulo, Serafim.","Italian: probably from a short form of a personal name ending with the hypocoristic suffix <i>-ello</i>, such as <i>Giacomello</i> from   Giacomo  .","Portuguese: variant of   Melo  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Giacomo","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Domenico, Gino, Salvatore.","Italian: from the personal name <i>Giacomo</i>, from Latin <i>Jacobus</i> via Late Latin <i>Jacomus</i> (see   James   and   Jacob  )."]},{"name":"Melle","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Heinz, Horst, Kurt, Otto.","Italian: habitational name from Melle in Cuneo province (Piedmont); in some cases possibly also a variant of a personal name such as   Mello   1.","Norwegian: probably a variant of   Mele  ."]},{"name":"Mellone","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Antonio, Emidio, Luigi, Pasquale.","Italian: from an augmentative of   Mello  ."]}]},{"name":"Marguerite","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Margaret  , also used in the English-speaking world, where its use has been reinforced by the fact that the name was adopted in the 19th century for a garden flower, a large cultivated variety of daisy. <i>Margaret</i> was earlier used in English as a dialect word denoting the ox-eye daisy, and the French equivalent was borrowed into English just in time to catch the vogue for deriving girls' names from vocabulary words denoting flowers.  See also  Daisy ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Marguerite de Mello was born in 1220, in Lézinnes, Yonne, Burgundy, France. She had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Guillaume I de Villehardouin. She died on 21 February 1254, at the age of 34, and was buried in France."},"et":{"1220–21 de fevereiro de 1254":"1220–21. veebruar 1254","1210–1246":"1210–1246","1235–1312":"1235–1312","1240–1307":"1240–1307","1244–1264":"1244–1264","1220–1254":"1220–1254","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1240":"1240","21 de fevereiro de 1254":"21. veebruar 1254","1235":"1235","1312":"1312","1246":"1246","Abt 1244":"umbes 1244","1244":"1244","1254":"1254","1210":"1210","8 juin 1246":"8. juuni 1246","1307":"1307",", LEZINNES, Yonne, France":"Lézinnes, Yonne, Bourgogne, Prantsusmaa","Larrivour, France":"Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa","Lézinnes, Yonne, Bourgogne, França":"Lézinnes, Yonne, Bourgogne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1220–21 de fevereiro de 1254":"1220–21. helmikuuta 1254","1210–1246":"1210–1246","1235–1312":"1235–1312","1240–1307":"1240–1307","1244–1264":"1244–1264","1220–1254":"1220–1254","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1240":"1240","21 de fevereiro de 1254":"21. helmikuuta 1254","1235":"1235","1312":"1312","1246":"1246","Abt 1244":"noin 1244","1244":"1244","1254":"1254","1210":"1210","8 juin 1246":"8. kesäkuuta 1246","1307":"1307",", LEZINNES, Yonne, France":"Lézinnes, Yonne, Bourgogne, Ranska","Larrivour, France":"Ranska","France":"Ranska","Lézinnes, Yonne, Bourgogne, França":"Lézinnes, Yonne, Bourgogne, Ranska"},"fr":{"1220–21 de fevereiro de 1254":"1220–21 fé